# Examples

Markers inside code fences are examples, not definitions:

```markdown
r[example.one]
This is how you write a requirement.
```

And inline too: `r[example.two]` shouldn't count.

But this one outside the fence does:

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-real.requirement"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-real.requirement">real.requirement</a></div>

This is real.
